		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=159293"><span id=>Trellium</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />399 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [2.85]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Trellium&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>1) Your choice. I prefer separate directories so that one EQ instance can have different options than the other (if they are on different hard drives, there is also often a performance advantage). One is my main character, the other is the dumb bot. One has more models turned on, uses a higher frame rate setting, and has the actor clip plane further out. The bot version has all those at minimum needed.<br><br>2) My systems dual box, and two of those are below your specs. It depends a lot on the zone. Also, I often just have a bazaar mule on as the alternate char though. Zoning times tend to be longer when two chars zone at the same time.<br><br>3) I use EQwindows, prefer it to standard EQ. I hate having to hit the alt key and tab to switch instances, then release the alt key and start some macro keye, and then hit alt key and tab again to go back. EQwindows lets you assign the keys, so for me to get my bot to start a nuke macro is as easy as pressing the three keys `1` (` is set to switch instances, 1 is the hot key macro). EQwindows also lets you name the session, so each EQ running has a unique name in the task bar. It also lets you bypass the patcher as an option.<br><br>4) Its a much bigger pain to equip two characters than one. But, the actually botting is easy compared to tha time taken to level up/AA/equip a second character.<br><br>5) Learn to simplify all the bot actions. Make macros that target your main char, stands up (/sit off) and then does a /follow. Make others that nuke, and wait, then sit. Make keys to assist specific people in your group/raid. Other things you will figure out as you go, to make life easier.<br><br>6) start one, go past the patcher (anywhere from the EULA screen onward), then start the second copy of EQ.<br><br><i><span class="sm">Edited, Wed Mar 30 15:16:43 2005 by Trellium</span class="sm"></i></p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td></tr></table>
